  <exercise xml:id="empty-7">
    <statement>
      <p>Write the function <c>mean</c> which returns the average of a vector of numbers.</p>
    </statement>
    <program interactive="activecode" line-numbers="yes" xml:id="vectors_a9q_editor">
      <input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;
        ]]></input>
    </program>
    <solution>


    
                Below is one way to finish the program.  First we take the sum, then divide the sum by the number
                    of elements in nums.

    
    <program xml:id="vectors_a9a_editor" line-numbers="yes"><input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

double mean(const vector<double> nums) {
    double sum = 0;
    for (size_t i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i) {
        sum = sum + nums[i];
    }
    return sum/nums.size();
}
        ]]></input></program>

            

